In addition to the specific items checked above, I am requesting:

1. All bench conferences that were recorded and later read into the record or otherwise transcribed during the trial dates (2025-03-10 through 2025-03-13), particularly those addressing:
   - Objections to the admission of the defendant’s prior text messages;
   - Disputes over the wording of certain jury instructions on self-defense and credibility;
   - Any discussion of the Commonwealth’s late disclosure of supplemental body camera footage.

2. Any on-the-record discussions regarding jury questions and the court’s responses, including the brief return of the jury to the courtroom on 2025-03-13 at approximately 2:45 p.m. to ask for clarification on the elements of aggravated assault and the burden of proof.

3. Any on-the-record colloquies with the defendant concerning:
   - His decision not to accept the pre-trial plea offer that was briefly placed on the record on 2025-03-10 before jury selection;
   - His decision to testify in his own defense, including the full colloquy conducted by Judge Donnelly on 2025-03-12.

I am requesting these additional items to ensure that the Superior Court has a complete and accurate record of all substantive and procedural issues that may be raised on appeal, including challenges to evidentiary rulings, the adequacy of the jury instructions, and the knowing and voluntary nature of the defendant’s decisions regarding plea negotiations and trial testimony.
